529
00:25:06,875 --> 00:25:08,142
[radio turns off]

530
00:25:14,175 --> 00:25:16,407
[paperboy] Read all about it
in the <i>Telegram.</i>

531
00:25:16,409 --> 00:25:19,873
The Dodgers can stay if
the city will give 'em a yard.

532
00:25:19,875 --> 00:25:22,207
Read all about it
in the <i>Telegram.</i>

533
00:25:22,209 --> 00:25:25,474
The Dodgers can stay if
the city will give 'em a yard.

534
00:25:25,476 --> 00:25:27,340
[Julia] <i>All these
wide-necked apes,</i>

535
00:25:27,342 --> 00:25:29,641
<i>trackin' mud
through my apartment,</i>

536
00:25:29,643 --> 00:25:31,773
asking all kinds of questions

537
00:25:31,775 --> 00:25:33,407
and I told them,
"Christ, he's dead.

538
00:25:33,409 --> 00:25:35,173
What, are you gonna
arrest him?"

539
00:25:35,175 --> 00:25:37,641
Fuck you been?
Called you all morning.

540
00:25:37,643 --> 00:25:39,040
What the hell happened here?

541
00:25:39,042 --> 00:25:40,840
Danny had
an early run out to Belmont,

542
00:25:40,842 --> 00:25:42,073
came in, it was like this.

543
00:25:42,075 --> 00:25:43,906
Cops were at Frank's place,
too,

544
00:25:43,908 --> 00:25:45,340
- going through everything.
- If!

545
00:25:45,342 --> 00:25:46,707
They were going through
my underwear drawer

546
00:25:46,709 --> 00:25:48,240
and they were grinnin' at me

547
00:25:48,242 --> 00:25:49,507
while they were going through
my underwear drawer.

548
00:25:49,509 --> 00:25:50,973
We're gonna find out
who did this,

549
00:25:50,975 --> 00:25:51,940
get to the bottom of it.
Right, boys?

550
00:25:51,942 --> 00:25:53,007
I don't even want to know.

551
00:25:53,009 --> 00:25:54,674
Always with this cryptic shit,

552
00:25:54,676 --> 00:25:57,207
telling me he's into
something big this time

553
00:25:57,209 --> 00:26:00,240
and that he's gonna
change our situation,

554
00:26:00,242 --> 00:26:02,540
and then he goes
and gets whacked,

555
00:26:02,542 --> 00:26:06,107
and leaves me $4,000
in a savings and loan,

556
00:26:06,109 --> 00:26:09,806
and a drafty shithole
at Lookout Point,

557
00:26:09,808 --> 00:26:12,973
and this thriving operation!

558
00:26:12,975 --> 00:26:15,409
The fuck am I supposed to do
with this?

559
00:26:16,908 --> 00:26:18,276
[exhales]

560
00:26:19,175 --> 00:26:20,040
[sighs]

561
00:26:20,042 --> 00:26:22,607
Look, the way I see it,

562
00:26:22,609 --> 00:26:25,073
you guys work for me now.

563
00:26:25,075 --> 00:26:27,540
I know you all go way back
with him, longer than me,

564
00:26:27,542 --> 00:26:29,507
but that's just the way
it is for now.

565
00:26:29,509 --> 00:26:31,607
I know the car service
was mainly for the books,

566
00:26:31,609 --> 00:26:35,873
but we didn't talk much about
how he ran the snoop work.

567
00:26:35,875 --> 00:26:37,873
And I ain't interested.

568
00:26:37,875 --> 00:26:41,007
So, I'm puttin'
Tony in charge.

569
00:26:41,009 --> 00:26:42,906
He's gonna run
the business of it,

570
00:26:42,908 --> 00:26:44,773
and then he'll keep me
in the loop. Right?

571
00:26:44,775 --> 00:26:47,540
Sure, doll.
It's the right thing.

572
00:26:47,542 --> 00:26:49,107
Sure.

573
00:26:49,109 --> 00:26:50,940
You want me to walk you home?

574
00:26:50,942 --> 00:26:52,707
No, thanks.

575
00:26:52,709 --> 00:26:55,940
I'm gonna go stay with
my sister for a little bit.

576
00:26:55,942 --> 00:26:58,440
I have to go figure out
my future.

577
00:26:58,442 --> 00:27:00,942
But give me a call. Okay?

578
00:27:01,709 --> 00:27:03,409
You know, for an update?

579
00:27:07,376 --> 00:27:09,773
- Hey, Julia.
- Hey, Lionel.

580
00:27:09,775 --> 00:27:11,107
Can't you ever cut that out?

581
00:27:11,109 --> 00:27:13,240
Touch it, Bailey!
I'm sorry.

582
00:27:13,242 --> 00:27:14,440
For once?

583
00:27:14,442 --> 00:27:15,374
If!

584
00:27:15,376 --> 00:27:17,442
- [stammers] I'm...
- Jesus.

585
00:27:19,975 --> 00:27:21,175
[Lionel] What?

586
00:27:21,808 --> 00:27:23,307
[Lionel sighs]

587
00:27:23,309 --> 00:27:25,908
Fuckin' assholes even took
the tank off the john.

588
00:27:28,975 --> 00:27:30,340
All right, forget that,
do it later.

589
00:27:30,342 --> 00:27:32,374
Right now,
just the four of us...

590
00:27:32,376 --> 00:27:34,340
Does anybody know
what Frank was into on this?

591
00:27:34,342 --> 00:27:36,073
He just said to meet him
for a sit.

592
00:27:36,075 --> 00:27:37,741
He didn't even make it
like it was a big thing.

593
00:27:37,743 --> 00:27:38,906
- He was nervous, though.
- Nervous how?

594
00:27:38,908 --> 00:27:40,140
He wasn't nervous.

595
00:27:40,142 --> 00:27:41,574
Were you on that line,
dumb shit?

596
00:27:41,576 --> 00:27:42,707
I'm telling you, I heard it,
he was nervous.

597
00:27:42,709 --> 00:27:44,407
Nervous Nellie!

598
00:27:44,409 --> 00:27:45,607
It was in his voice.

599
00:27:45,609 --> 00:27:47,641
He was trying to make a play
on those guys.

600
00:27:47,643 --> 00:27:49,374
There's somethin' goin' down a
week from Thursday that's big.

601
00:27:49,376 --> 00:27:51,107
And they were not happy
about what he found.

602
00:27:51,109 --> 00:27:52,773
Obviously.
They whacked him for it.

603
00:27:52,775 --> 00:27:54,374
Crack whacker! No,

604
00:27:54,376 --> 00:27:56,340
I don't think they meant to.
I think it was a mistake.

605
00:27:56,342 --> 00:27:58,173
When they shot him,
I think they fucked up,

606
00:27:58,175 --> 00:28:00,007
now they're stuck
looking for what he found.

607
00:28:00,009 --> 00:28:02,042
[Tony] Big fuckin' riddle.
Jesus H.

608
00:28:02,975 --> 00:28:04,542
All right, I'm gonna say this.

609
00:28:05,908 --> 00:28:08,073
I loved the guy.

610
00:28:08,075 --> 00:28:09,940
And when we were
in that fuckin' hellhole,

611
00:28:09,942 --> 00:28:11,274
he saw somethin' in us,

612
00:28:11,276 --> 00:28:13,207
threw us a line,
taught us how to operate,

613
00:28:13,209 --> 00:28:14,707
but he never cut us in
all the way.

614
00:28:14,709 --> 00:28:16,307
And he played his own games.

615
00:28:16,309 --> 00:28:18,207
And I'm not stickin' my nose
around his dead cards,

616
00:28:18,209 --> 00:28:20,476
risk ending up
on a slab for it.

617
00:28:23,175 --> 00:28:24,906
I say we got
a lot of bills to pay,

618
00:28:24,908 --> 00:28:26,707
and we ought to
just get at it.

619
00:28:26,709 --> 00:28:28,073
You owe him
more than that, T.

620
00:28:28,075 --> 00:28:29,707
Yeah, well, you figure out
what the fuck

621
00:28:29,709 --> 00:28:31,641
it was all about,
you let us know.

622
00:28:31,643 --> 00:28:35,040
All right? Meantime, I gotta
finish up on the rabbi's wife.

623
00:28:35,042 --> 00:28:36,707
She's banging a butcher
who ain't kosher

624
00:28:36,709 --> 00:28:38,407
and I think he's really gonna
give her the boot this time,

625
00:28:38,409 --> 00:28:40,307
and that's gonna be
the last of that ride.

626
00:28:40,309 --> 00:28:43,073
I want Gil sitting on
that Gunderson fraud thing.

627
00:28:43,075 --> 00:28:45,474
- I'm on Gunderson.
- Yeah, well, I want Gil on it!

628
00:28:45,476 --> 00:28:46,707
- Why?
- Because

629
00:28:46,709 --> 00:28:48,274
when we make that bust,

630
00:28:48,276 --> 00:28:49,940
the insurance company's gonna
want us to go down there,

631
00:28:49,942 --> 00:28:51,173
show the pictures
to his lawyer,

632
00:28:51,175 --> 00:28:52,607
and I wanna make
a good impression.

633
00:28:52,609 --> 00:28:53,940
Okay? Frank ain't here
to cover for you anymore.

634
00:28:53,942 --> 00:28:55,340
- Fraud fag!
- Like I said,

635
00:28:55,342 --> 00:28:57,240
Gil's on it.
Danny will back me on nights,

636
00:28:57,242 --> 00:28:59,240
and, Lionel, you pick up
the car slack for him,

637
00:28:59,242 --> 00:29:01,075
just until something new
comes in.

638
00:29:02,309 --> 00:29:03,806
It's cold. We're gonna have
a lot of calls,

639
00:29:03,808 --> 00:29:05,840
and we need that business.
Fuck!

640
00:29:05,842 --> 00:29:07,775
Now, come on, let's clean up.

641
00:29:09,676 --> 00:29:11,207
[door closes]

642
00:29:11,209 --> 00:29:13,806
[Lionel] <i>Tony, and Coney,
and Danny, and me...</i>

643
00:29:13,808 --> 00:29:15,507
<i>before we were Minna's men,</i>

644
00:29:15,509 --> 00:29:17,840
<i>we were just dead-end kids
at the Catholic orphanage.</i>

645
00:29:17,842 --> 00:29:19,641
[phone ringing]

646
00:29:19,643 --> 00:29:21,140
Invest-ahead!

647
00:29:21,142 --> 00:29:24,340
<i>I was worse in there.
A total freakshow.</i>

648
00:29:24,342 --> 00:29:26,309
<i>No one knew
what to do with it.</i>

649
00:29:27,409 --> 00:29:29,274
L&L.

650
00:29:29,276 --> 00:29:31,741
Yeah, we have cars available.
Where would you like to go?

651
00:29:31,743 --> 00:29:34,040
<i>The nuns thought they were
gonna beat it out of me.</i>

652
00:29:34,042 --> 00:29:35,507
<i>One of 'em in particular.</i>

653
00:29:35,509 --> 00:29:36,873
<i>Till Tony grabbed
the paddle from her</i>

654
00:29:36,875 --> 00:29:38,407
<i>and said if she hit me again,</i>

655
00:29:38,409 --> 00:29:40,374
<i>he was gonna
give it to her twice as hard.</i>

656
00:29:40,376 --> 00:29:42,507
<i>Coney and Danny were standing
behind him when he said it</i>

657
00:29:42,509 --> 00:29:44,173
<i>and she knew
they weren't bluffin'.</i>

658
00:29:44,175 --> 00:29:46,842
<i>After that,
I was in their crew.</i>

659
00:29:52,576 --> 00:29:53,775
If!

660
00:30:03,609 --> 00:30:05,476
[phone ringing]

661
00:30:06,975 --> 00:30:08,808
- L&L.
- [man] <i>Who am I speaking to?</i>

662
00:30:09,209 --> 00:30:11,140
Ass-rog!

663
00:30:11,142 --> 00:30:13,073
This is Lionel Essrog.
I'm associate...

664
00:30:13,075 --> 00:30:15,042
- [line disconnects]
- Hello?

665
00:30:22,342 --> 00:30:23,875
[whispering]

666
00:30:24,576 --> 00:30:26,109
Formosa.

667
00:30:26,775 --> 00:30:28,175
Formosa.

668
00:30:30,908 --> 00:30:32,474
<i>Frank was just
from the neighborhood.</i>

669
00:30:32,476 --> 00:30:33,806
<i>He was smart.</i>

670
00:30:33,808 --> 00:30:35,140
<i>Everybody knew
he was goin' places.</i>

671
00:30:35,142 --> 00:30:36,540
<i>Everybody liked him.</i>

672
00:30:36,542 --> 00:30:38,641
For my ass, Bailey!

673
00:30:38,643 --> 00:30:40,374
<i>He was friends
with one of the priests,</i>

674
00:30:40,376 --> 00:30:43,007
<i>and he heard I had a thing
for remembering.</i>

675
00:30:43,009 --> 00:30:45,107
<i>Numbers and words and things,</i>

676
00:30:45,109 --> 00:30:47,607
<i>and he had uses for that.</i>

677
00:30:47,609 --> 00:30:50,274
<i>He was the one that taught me
how to use my head,</i>

678
00:30:50,276 --> 00:30:52,242
<i>get it under control,
make it work for me.</i>

679
00:30:53,709 --> 00:30:56,374
<i>He took all of us
under his wing, eventually.</i>

680
00:30:56,376 --> 00:30:59,042
<i>Gave us a place
in this shitty world.</i>

681
00:31:08,542 --> 00:31:09,542
[gunshot]

682
00:31:11,775 --> 00:31:12,975
[gunshot]

683
00:31:16,743 --> 00:31:17,806
- [Danny] Lionel?
- If!

684
00:31:17,808 --> 00:31:19,873
Oh, Jesus Christ!

685
00:31:19,875 --> 00:31:21,274
You scared the hell out of me.

686
00:31:21,276 --> 00:31:22,674
I thought
I was lookin' at a ghost.

687
00:31:22,676 --> 00:31:25,040
- What are you doin'?
- Spinnin'.

688
00:31:25,042 --> 00:31:27,140
- You back already?
- Nah, I'm on a round trip.

689
00:31:27,142 --> 00:31:28,842
I gotta go back soon.

690
00:31:29,342 --> 00:31:31,007
You okay?

691
00:31:31,009 --> 00:31:33,973
I should have never let him
get in that car.

692
00:31:33,975 --> 00:31:35,540
I think I blew it, Danny.

693
00:31:35,542 --> 00:31:38,240
I had a sergeant once
in the Bulge. Told me,

694
00:31:38,242 --> 00:31:40,374
"Sometimes you do everything
you're supposed to,

695
00:31:40,376 --> 00:31:43,075
and it all still goes
to shit." Hmm?

696
00:31:43,808 --> 00:31:45,540
It ain't on you, bud.

697
00:31:45,542 --> 00:31:46,908
Thanks, D.

698
00:31:47,476 --> 00:31:48,509
Any calls?

699
00:31:49,442 --> 00:31:50,808
Yeah. Oh, shit!

700
00:31:52,409 --> 00:31:53,540
I gotta go.

701
00:31:53,542 --> 00:31:54,875
I got a 2:30.

702
00:31:56,242 --> 00:31:57,707
Hey...

703
00:31:57,709 --> 00:32:00,440
did you ever hear Frank mention
anything about "Formosa"?

704
00:32:00,442 --> 00:32:01,607
Like the Jap island?

705
00:32:01,609 --> 00:32:03,942
Nah. He was wounded
and out before then.

706
00:32:04,576 --> 00:32:06,040
Hmm.

707
00:32:06,042 --> 00:32:09,007
There is that joint, Formosa,
in, uh, Midtown.

708
00:32:09,009 --> 00:32:11,542
I took Linda there
to see Chet Baker once.

709
00:32:14,409 --> 00:32:15,973
[Lionel] <i>Frank didn't have
to cover for me.</i>

710
00:32:15,975 --> 00:32:17,940
<i>He just never put me
into situations</i>

711
00:32:17,942 --> 00:32:19,773
<i>that were gonna
punch my buttons.</i>

712
00:32:19,775 --> 00:32:22,540
<i>Talkin' to people, gettin'
information out of 'em,</i>

713
00:32:22,542 --> 00:32:24,274
<i>that's the bread and butter
of the trade,</i>

714
00:32:24,276 --> 00:32:26,107
<i>but never my strong suit.</i>

715
00:32:26,109 --> 00:32:28,674
<i>Especially if a girl shows up
in the mix</i>

716
00:32:28,676 --> 00:32:31,274
<i>and, in this line of work,
they usually do.</i>

717
00:32:31,276 --> 00:32:32,641
[bartender] Music's at 7:00.

718
00:32:32,643 --> 00:32:35,040
Yeah, could I get
an early one? Whiskey, neat?

719
00:32:35,042 --> 00:32:37,040
- Irish?
- Sure.

720
00:32:37,042 --> 00:32:39,474
Say, are you in here regular?

721
00:32:39,476 --> 00:32:41,040
Most of my life.

722
00:32:41,042 --> 00:32:43,007
You ever seen this guy
come in?

723
00:32:43,009 --> 00:32:44,973
Name's Frank Minna.

724
00:32:44,975 --> 00:32:46,207
Seen him around?

725
00:32:46,209 --> 00:32:48,773
Everybody looks like
everybody to me,

