00:55:26,942 --> 00:55:28,840
Gotta show this
to Bill Lieberman.

1215
00:55:28,842 --> 00:55:32,376
He's gonna want to see this before
Randolph speaks, believe me.

1216
00:55:36,476 --> 00:55:37,973
[union boss speaker]
Thank you. Thank you,

1217
00:55:37,975 --> 00:55:40,940
ladies and gentlemen.
Please settle down

1218
00:55:40,942 --> 00:55:43,773
and lend
your serious attention.

1219
00:55:43,775 --> 00:55:45,140
Don't worry. We'll celebrate.

1220
00:55:45,142 --> 00:55:48,607
We're gonna eat like
only we know how to eat.

1221
00:55:48,609 --> 00:55:51,707
Tonight's celebration
is made very special

1222
00:55:51,709 --> 00:55:53,407
by our guest of honor,

1223
00:55:53,409 --> 00:55:54,973
a brother to our trade...

1224
00:55:54,975 --> 00:55:56,407
- Hey, Gleason, right?
- Hey.

1225
00:55:56,409 --> 00:55:57,973
...who would rightly be hailed
this country's

1226
00:55:57,975 --> 00:55:59,641
- master builder...
- Nice threads.

1227
00:55:59,643 --> 00:56:03,307
...or "the Great Dirt Mover"

1228
00:56:03,309 --> 00:56:04,973
- as he likes to be called.
- [laughter]

1229
00:56:04,975 --> 00:56:06,973
Don't let them see you
pull out a notebook.

1230
00:56:06,975 --> 00:56:11,207
Tonight, it's
"Press: Forget about it."

1231
00:56:11,209 --> 00:56:13,307
[union boss speaker] We'd have
to look to the Caesars

1232
00:56:13,309 --> 00:56:17,574
and pharaohs to find men
with a scale of vision

1233
00:56:17,576 --> 00:56:19,073
to compare with his.

1234
00:56:19,075 --> 00:56:20,707
- A great man.
- If!

1235
00:56:20,709 --> 00:56:22,240
A man of history,

1236
00:56:22,242 --> 00:56:26,773
serving the people of
this city for over 25 years,

1237
00:56:26,775 --> 00:56:29,674
Moses Randolph!

1238
00:56:29,676 --> 00:56:31,542
[applause]

1239
00:56:38,743 --> 00:56:41,607
Jeez, you'd think
Patton showed up.

1240
00:56:41,609 --> 00:56:44,940
He pays one and a half times
union rate on all of his jobs.

1241
00:56:44,942 --> 00:56:47,175
They'd pave over
their mothers for him.

1242
00:56:48,409 --> 00:56:49,808
Thank you, Joe.

1243
00:56:50,576 --> 00:56:53,140
Tonight, over 300 years

1244
00:56:53,142 --> 00:56:55,407
since the founding
of this great city,

1245
00:56:55,409 --> 00:56:59,173
we recommit ourselves
to the ancient truth

1246
00:56:59,175 --> 00:57:01,440
that it is not knowledge,

1247
00:57:01,442 --> 00:57:03,274
but action and enterprise

1248
00:57:03,276 --> 00:57:07,474
which are the engine
and objective in life.

1249
00:57:07,476 --> 00:57:09,374
Clever men come and go,

1250
00:57:09,376 --> 00:57:13,140
but for every dozen of them
with their big ideas,

1251
00:57:13,142 --> 00:57:15,942
there is not more than one
that can execute them.

1252
00:57:16,775 --> 00:57:18,007
I look around this room,

1253
00:57:18,009 --> 00:57:19,707
I don't see
a lot of bright boys

1254
00:57:19,709 --> 00:57:23,507
or goodie-goodie progressives
with their paralyzing ideals.

1255
00:57:23,509 --> 00:57:25,042
[laughter]

1256
00:57:26,009 --> 00:57:28,042
I see the men of my tribe.

1257
00:57:29,009 --> 00:57:31,073
The men who get things done.

1258
00:57:31,075 --> 00:57:33,840
The doers that make
this country great!

1259
00:57:33,842 --> 00:57:35,908
[applause]

1260
00:57:36,709 --> 00:57:38,674
To be honored by you

1261
00:57:38,676 --> 00:57:42,808
is all the affirmation or
payment I shall ever seek.

1262
00:57:43,808 --> 00:57:45,342
I celebrate you

1263
00:57:46,242 --> 00:57:47,440
and I thank you.

1264
00:57:47,442 --> 00:57:49,207
[men] Hear, hear!

1265
00:57:49,209 --> 00:57:50,542
[applause]

1266
00:58:06,808 --> 00:58:08,342
[inaudible conversation]

1267
00:58:13,542 --> 00:58:15,075
[whispering indistinctly]

1268
00:58:22,142 --> 00:58:23,440
I'll catch you
on the next one.

1269
00:58:23,442 --> 00:58:24,442
All right.

1270
00:58:56,276 --> 00:58:57,540
You finished it?

1271
00:58:57,542 --> 00:58:59,340
Best work I've done.

1272
00:58:59,342 --> 00:59:02,973
A total modernization of
the state's electrical grid.

1273
00:59:02,975 --> 00:59:05,975
And it's a scale
that only you can get done.

1274
00:59:11,242 --> 00:59:12,641
Clean yourself up,
for Christ sakes.

1275
00:59:12,643 --> 00:59:14,240
How? With what?

1276
00:59:14,242 --> 00:59:15,973
Hey, not a fuckin' word
out of you about any of that.

1277
00:59:15,975 --> 00:59:17,307
You bring that up to me
ever again,

1278
00:59:17,309 --> 00:59:18,574
I'm gonna close you out
for good.

1279
00:59:18,576 --> 00:59:20,173
Moses, I'm so far out,

1280
00:59:20,175 --> 00:59:22,707
I'm doing piecework
for kids fresh out of school.

1281
00:59:22,709 --> 00:59:25,073
[Moses] You whip up a crowd
against me like that ever again,

1282
00:59:25,075 --> 00:59:26,440
I'm gonna take your big idea,

1283
00:59:26,442 --> 00:59:27,873
I'll throw it
on the fuckin' scrap heap.

1284
00:59:27,875 --> 00:59:29,940
- Is that what you want?
- No, no.

1285
00:59:29,942 --> 00:59:32,540
Okay, I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

1286
00:59:32,542 --> 00:59:34,340
None of that matters.

1287
00:59:34,342 --> 00:59:36,842
Just read it.

1288
00:59:38,676 --> 00:59:39,975
I'll read it.

1289
00:59:41,709 --> 00:59:44,242
[Lionel] <i>What makes a person
go against their own brother?</i>

1290
00:59:45,376 --> 00:59:47,007
<i>All my life,
I'd never had a family,</i>

1291
00:59:47,009 --> 00:59:48,607
<i>so I never could
understand people</i>

1292
00:59:48,609 --> 00:59:51,140
<i>who did and let it get ugly.</i>

1293
00:59:51,142 --> 00:59:55,107
<i>My crazy brain was tellin' me I
should keep pullin' on that thread,</i>

1294
00:59:55,109 --> 00:59:56,507
<i>but whatever Frank found,</i>

1295
00:59:56,509 --> 00:59:58,407
<i>he found it
following the girl.</i>

1296
00:59:58,409 --> 01:00:01,009
<i>So, I just kept chasin'
his footsteps.</i>

1297
01:00:19,626 --> 01:00:20,825
Hello?

1298
01:00:22,793 --> 01:00:23,992
Hello?

1299
01:01:03,584 --> 01:01:05,651
- [woman sobbing]
- [indistinct chatter]

1300
01:01:30,550 --> 01:01:31,550
If!

1301
01:01:33,350 --> 01:01:35,217
Keep it together, Freakshow.

1302
01:01:42,851 --> 01:01:43,851
Jesus.

1303
01:01:46,751 --> 01:01:48,815
- You lookin' for somethin'?
- Help, Bailey!

1304
01:01:48,817 --> 01:01:50,148
Ah, shit.

1305
01:01:50,150 --> 01:01:51,415
What, you think you can just
walk into people's homes?

1306
01:01:51,417 --> 01:01:52,815
No, I was lookin' for someone.

1307
01:01:52,817 --> 01:01:54,082
I didn't think
anybody lived here.

1308
01:01:54,084 --> 01:01:55,248
Oh, someone lives here.

1309
01:01:55,250 --> 01:01:56,482
- My momma lives here.
- Sure.

1310
01:01:56,484 --> 01:01:58,248
- At least, she's tryin' to.
- If!

1311
01:01:58,250 --> 01:01:59,548
Who you with?

1312
01:01:59,550 --> 01:02:01,049
- Huh?
- I hope you're with Belmont.

1313
01:02:01,051 --> 01:02:02,851
Yeah, yeah, Belmont.
Who else?

1314
01:02:03,717 --> 01:02:04,784
[thuds]

1315
01:02:07,250 --> 01:02:08,615
[Laura] What is going on?

1316
01:02:08,617 --> 01:02:10,417
[man] We got ourselves
an intruder.

1317
01:02:11,951 --> 01:02:14,315
- How hard did you hit him?
- I barely tapped him.

1318
01:02:14,317 --> 01:02:15,749
Fool slipped
and hit his own head.

1319
01:02:15,751 --> 01:02:16,751
[Lionel] If!

1320
01:02:17,717 --> 01:02:19,615
"If" what?

1321
01:02:19,617 --> 01:02:21,448
I'll tell you what, "if"...

1322
01:02:21,450 --> 01:02:23,148
you better explain who you are

1323
01:02:23,150 --> 01:02:24,684
if you want to
walk out of here.

1324
01:02:26,283 --> 01:02:27,548
Have I seen you before?

1325
01:02:27,550 --> 01:02:29,049
[Lionel] Yeah,
my name is Jake Gleason.

1326
01:02:29,051 --> 01:02:30,148
It's a misunderstanding,
all right?

1327
01:02:30,150 --> 01:02:31,749
I'm a reporter.

1328
01:02:31,751 --> 01:02:34,415
I was at the Hamilton Housing
hearing the other night.

1329
01:02:34,417 --> 01:02:36,049
I called the committee
this morning.

1330
01:02:36,051 --> 01:02:37,882
I came out here
looking for you.

1331
01:02:37,884 --> 01:02:40,482
He the one that said he's with
those racketeering sons of bitches.

1332
01:02:40,484 --> 01:02:42,016
They stole her fridge.

1333
01:02:42,018 --> 01:02:44,749
They stole her copper pipes.
Man, what you expect?

1334
01:02:44,751 --> 01:02:47,382
First, they put up a notice says
the house will be condemned.

1335
01:02:47,384 --> 01:02:49,215
It's not true,
but that scares out

1336
01:02:49,217 --> 01:02:50,849
about half
and they sell for cheap.

1337
01:02:50,851 --> 01:02:53,348
Then they come in and take
the nice old family homes,

1338
01:02:53,350 --> 01:02:55,148
chop 'em into four
and rent 'em up.

1339
01:02:55,150 --> 01:02:56,982
Folks who don't leave,
they harass,

1340
01:02:56,984 --> 01:02:58,548
turn the heat off,

1341
01:02:58,550 --> 01:03:00,749
come in to do repairs
and steal copper pipe instead.

1342
01:03:00,751 --> 01:03:04,281
The city sold property worth
$15 million for 500,000

1343
01:03:04,283 --> 01:03:07,215
to take the risk of having to
build the federal projects.

1344
01:03:07,217 --> 01:03:08,815
They haven't even
submitted plans,

1345
01:03:08,817 --> 01:03:10,882
just milked it
till it really is a slum.

1346
01:03:10,884 --> 01:03:12,882
Slammer for the slum lords,
Bailey!

1347
01:03:12,884 --> 01:03:14,448
- Ah...
- Oh, what?

1348
01:03:14,450 --> 01:03:15,982
You're one of those who thinks
we're just agitating?

1349
01:03:15,984 --> 01:03:18,382
Making it up like some
Negro propaganda conspiracy?

1350
01:03:18,384 --> 01:03:20,315
No, no, look, look, look.
I got a condition, okay?

1351
01:03:20,317 --> 01:03:23,417
It makes me say funny things,
but I'm not trying to be funny.

1352
01:03:53,834 --> 01:03:55,234
I'm really not. I'm listenin'.

1353
01:03:56,234 --> 01:03:57,598
Where's everybody go?

1354
01:03:57,600 --> 01:04:01,399
[sighs] Mostly just disappear.
Fade away.

1355
01:04:01,401 --> 01:04:03,032
200,000 in two years,

1356
01:04:03,034 --> 01:04:04,999
just from this part
of Brooklyn.

1357
01:04:05,001 --> 01:04:07,299
- Mostly Negro. Latino.
- Yeah,

1358
01:04:07,301 --> 01:04:09,132
but Horowitz said they did it
up in East Tremont, too.

1359
01:04:09,134 --> 01:04:10,865
- Same thing?
- Yeah, they did it

1360
01:04:10,867 --> 01:04:13,165
to a few Jews, too,
but not systematic like this.

1361
01:04:13,167 --> 01:04:14,798
How many parks, do you think,
have been built

1362
01:04:14,800 --> 01:04:16,832
in this city since
he's been commissioner?

1363
01:04:16,834 --> 01:04:18,598
255.

1364
01:04:18,600 --> 01:04:21,001
How many of those in Harlem,
you think?

1365
01:04:21,834 --> 01:04:22,965
One.

1366
01:04:22,967 --> 01:04:25,432
You build a new beach
for the people,

1367
01:04:25,434 --> 01:04:26,732
but the ones with no cars,

1368
01:04:26,734 --> 01:04:28,165
the poor ones,
the black and brown ones,

1369
01:04:28,167 --> 01:04:30,399
how are they gonna get
to the parks and beaches?

1370
01:04:30,401 --> 01:04:32,232
Public bus.

1371
01:04:32,234 --> 01:04:36,032
Guess how high they just built
the overpasses on the new parkway?

1372
01:04:36,034 --> 01:04:38,865
One foot too low
for a bus to clear.

1373
01:04:38,867 --> 01:04:40,032
Come on.

1374
01:04:40,034 --> 01:04:41,765
Look, forget whether
it's discrimination.

1375
01:04:41,767 --> 01:04:43,366
The federal government and
the city are being scammed.

1376
01:04:43,368 --> 01:04:45,631
There's supposed to be
relocation services,

1377
01:04:45,633 --> 01:04:47,299
company's got
a $2 million contract

1378
01:04:47,301 --> 01:04:49,598
to handle it, but nobody
even answers the phone.

1379
01:04:49,600 --> 01:04:51,165
Call the city,
they say these folks

1380
01:04:51,167 --> 01:04:52,832
are on the list for
the new public housing,

1381
01:04:52,834 --> 01:04:54,199
- but then it never gets built.
- You know more

1382
01:04:54,201 --> 01:04:55,798
than any secretary
I ever met in my life.

1383
01:04:55,800 --> 01:04:58,498
Secretary? Who told you that?

1384
01:04:58,500 --> 01:05:00,132
I got a law degree, you know?

1385
01:05:00,134 --> 01:05:02,466
I'll pass the bar
first time I sit, too.

1386
01:05:02,468 --> 01:05:04,332
Okay, then. Sorry.

1387
01:05:04,334 --> 01:05:05,932
How are you gonna write about it
all if you don't even take a note?

1388
01:05:05,934 --> 01:05:07,732
What, "$2 million
for relocation services,

1389
01:05:07,734 --> 01:05:09,299
bridges a foot too low
for the buses,

1390
01:05:09,301 --> 01:05:10,798
one out of 255 parks,

1391
01:05:10,800 --> 01:05:12,665
15 million in property
for 500K,

1392
01:05:12,667 --> 01:05:15,898
200,000 people
in Fort Greene alone." That?

1393
01:05:15,900 --> 01:05:17,765
I never forget anything,
believe me.

1394
01:05:17,767 --> 01:05:19,201
Not a single word.

1395
01:05:21,134 --> 01:05:24,165
I'm really sorry. [stammers]
I can't help it, I got a...

1396
01:05:24,167 --> 01:05:25,531
It's okay. [sighs]

1397
01:05:25,533 --> 01:05:28,265
Just write about it, please.

1398
01:05:28,267 --> 01:05:29,932
What happens to poor people
in this city

1399
01:05:29,934 --> 01:05:32,432
wasn't news yesterday
and it won't be tomorrow,

1400
01:05:32,434 --> 01:05:35,732
but you'd think somebody'd
care what happens to Brooklyn.

1401
01:05:35,734 --> 01:05:38,034
It's only the biggest city
on Earth.

1402
01:05:39,201 --> 01:05:41,032
[sighs]

1403
01:05:41,034 --> 01:05:42,067
Where you live?

1404
01:05:43,334 --> 01:05:45,199
- Harlem.
- Hmm.

1405
01:05:45,201 --> 01:05:47,199
This is me.

1406
01:05:47,201 --> 01:05:48,867
You want me
to give you a ride?

1407
01:05:50,468 --> 01:05:51,565
Come on,
the trains will be mobbed.

1408
01:05:51,567 --> 01:05:52,767
I'll give you a ride.

1409
01:05:54,034 --> 01:05:55,034
Come on.

1410
01:06:26,034 --> 01:06:29,165
Bebop, Bailey, in the
Metropolitan Bopera House!

1411
01:06:29,167 --> 01:06:30,965
[sighs] Oh, God.

1412
01:06:30,967 --> 01:06:33,498
- [chuckling]
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

1413
01:06:33,500 --> 01:06:35,865
Don't be sorry.
It's kinda funny.

1414
01:06:35,867 --> 01:06:39,900
Yeah? Well, hang around a little
while, and see what you think.

1415
01:06:44,267 --> 01:06:45,267
If!

1416
01:06:46,201 --> 01:06:47,832
What is all that, anyway?

1417
01:06:47,834 --> 01:06:51,199
I don't know.
I never got a name for it.

1418
01:06:51,201 --> 01:06:53,832
It's like a piece in my head broke
off and got a life of its own

1419
01:06:53,834 --> 01:06:56,867
and then just decided to
keep joyridin' me for kicks.

1420
01:06:57,500 --> 01:06:59,598
Kicks and tics!

1421
01:06:59,600 --> 01:07:02,232
Licks and tics!
Sorry. [inhales deeply]

1422
01:07:02,234 --> 01:07:03,598
- It's okay.
- [sighs]

1423
01:07:03,600 --> 01:07:06,466
It's like living
with an anarchist, you know,

1424
01:07:06,468 --> 01:07:10,366
but the funny thing is, it also has
to have everything in its right place.

1425
01:07:10,368 --> 01:07:14,399
Like, things have to be ordered
and lined up just right.

1426
01:07:14,401 --> 01:07:17,299
Everything has to sound
just right or else it really,

1427
01:07:17,301 --> 01:07:19,999
it'll really put me into knots
until I fix it.

1428
01:07:20,001 --> 01:07:22,466
Like, I'm talkin' to you
right now, right?

1429
01:07:22,468 --> 01:07:23,932
But that part of my head,

1430
01:07:23,934 --> 01:07:26,698
it's worryin' that the bills
in my wallet

1431
01:07:26,700 --> 01:07:28,498
aren't lined up all in
the right sequence,

1432
01:07:28,500 --> 01:07:30,032
and it's sayin',

1433
01:07:30,034 --> 01:07:31,432
"Stop talkin' to this girl,
and deal with this."

1434
01:07:31,434 --> 01:07:33,232
It's not fair.

1435
01:07:33,234 --> 01:07:37,001
Hey, we all got
our daily battles, right?

1436
01:07:38,767 --> 01:07:40,201
Yeah, fair enough.

1437
01:07:44,734 --> 01:07:46,165
Kiss her face all night,
Bailey!

1438
01:07:46,167 --> 01:07:49,099
- [laughing]
- Oh, God. [groans]

1439
01:07:49,101 --> 01:07:50,199
[sighs deeply]

1440
01:07:50,201 --> 01:07:51,432
I'm...

1441
01:07:51,434 --> 01:07:52,798
- I really am sorry.
- It's okay.

1442
01:07:52,800 --> 01:07:55,032
- I don't mean nothin' by it.
- Don't be sorry.

1443
01:07:55,034 --> 01:07:56,700
It's okay.

1444
01:08:19,633 --> 01:08:21,165
This is me.

1445
01:08:21,167 --> 01:08:23,466
What, up from that?
That must keep you up nights.

1446
01:08:23,468 --> 01:08:25,698
[chuckles]
My father owns the place.

1447
01:08:25,700 --> 01:08:28,965
I grew up falling asleep
in the back of clubs.

1448
01:08:28,967 --> 01:08:30,999
It's pretty hoppin'
for a Monday night.

1449
01:08:31,001 --> 01:08:33,201
Hottest band in the world,
all week.

1450
01:08:34,567 --> 01:08:36,132
Listen...

1451
01:08:36,134 --> 01:08:39,099
I gotta check
on one or two things,

1452
01:08:39,101 --> 01:08:42,500
but are you really interested
in what I was telling you?

1453
01:08:43,600 --> 01:08:46,765
Yeah, I came lookin' for you,
didn't I?

1454
01:08:46,767 --> 01:08:49,700
If you wanna come in,
I could give you a lot more.

1455
