1977
01:36:47,234 --> 01:36:49,165
He's gonna tell you
to pull yourself together

1978
01:36:49,167 --> 01:36:50,234
and get movin'.

1979
01:36:51,700 --> 01:36:53,299
And when you do,

1980
01:36:53,301 --> 01:36:55,498
you're gonna feel him smilin'
at you again, I promise.

1981
01:36:55,500 --> 01:36:56,867
[sobbing]

1982
01:37:04,700 --> 01:37:06,667
I really am sorry.

1983
01:37:11,834 --> 01:37:14,700
Why are you being
so nice to me?

1984
01:37:16,034 --> 01:37:18,267
Because I think
you're a good person.

1985
01:37:20,134 --> 01:37:21,932
You're tryin'
to make a difference.

1986
01:37:21,934 --> 01:37:24,132
You actually care about
what happens to other people.

1987
01:37:24,134 --> 01:37:25,631
I just...

1988
01:37:25,633 --> 01:37:27,667
Not many people can say that.

1989
01:37:28,734 --> 01:37:30,600
It's a good way to be.

1990
01:37:34,401 --> 01:37:35,600
You're sweet.

1991
01:37:39,167 --> 01:37:40,698
I don't think
that's how most people

1992
01:37:40,700 --> 01:37:41,999
usually describe me
when they meet me,

1993
01:37:42,001 --> 01:37:43,498
but I'm glad
that you think so.

1994
01:37:43,500 --> 01:37:44,932
[Laura chuckles]

1995
01:37:44,934 --> 01:37:47,232
[sniffles]

1996
01:37:47,234 --> 01:37:51,267
Anybody ever tell you
you talk in your sleep?

1997
01:37:54,368 --> 01:37:56,800
Um, I never slept
with anyone.

1998
01:37:58,700 --> 01:38:01,832
You never slept with anyone?

1999
