okay?

2033
01:40:01,001 --> 01:40:03,132
There's something big
out there

2034
01:40:03,134 --> 01:40:04,531
that has to do
with all this fraud

2035
01:40:04,533 --> 01:40:05,932
that you've been
diggin' around in.

2036
01:40:05,934 --> 01:40:08,565
I think it ties it right up
to Moses Randolph.

2037
01:40:08,567 --> 01:40:10,265
Do you know what it is?

2038
01:40:10,267 --> 01:40:12,432
No, no, I mean,

2039
01:40:12,434 --> 01:40:15,734
somebody's getting rich,
but no.

2040
01:40:16,934 --> 01:40:18,199
You gotta take this seriously.

2041
01:40:18,201 --> 01:40:19,665
If you're holdin' on
to some card

2042
01:40:19,667 --> 01:40:20,732
and you're waitin' to play it

2043
01:40:20,734 --> 01:40:21,898
to try to block that vote,

2044
01:40:21,900 --> 01:40:23,698
you're playin'
a dangerous game.

2045
01:40:23,700 --> 01:40:25,965
They already killed Frank,
they killed your father,

2046
01:40:25,967 --> 01:40:27,165
they did this to me
last night,

2047
01:40:27,167 --> 01:40:28,565
these people
aren't gonna stop.

2048
01:40:28,567 --> 01:40:29,665
What's Billy
got to do with it?

2049
01:40:29,667 --> 01:40:30,932
He knows something about it.

2050
01:40:30,934 --> 01:40:32,765
No. No, wait,
that's not possible.

2051
01:40:32,767 --> 01:40:34,565
He and my friend Frank
were working together on it.

2052
01:40:34,567 --> 01:40:35,965
He doesn't even...

2053
01:40:35,967 --> 01:40:39,065
He didn't even know
what I'm working on.

2054
01:40:39,067 --> 01:40:40,732
I have an uncle
who knows Gabby.

2055
01:40:40,734 --> 01:40:42,001
He got me that job.

2056
01:40:43,900 --> 01:40:45,265
You're not a reporter,
are you?

2057
01:40:45,267 --> 01:40:47,565
No, and my name's not Jake.
It's Lionel.

2058
01:40:47,567 --> 01:40:50,199
Look, Frank is
an investigator, okay?

2059
01:40:50,201 --> 01:40:51,698
That's who I worked for.

2060
01:40:51,700 --> 01:40:53,765
They hired him to keep tabs
on your committee.

2061
01:40:53,767 --> 01:40:55,898
He was following you.

2062
01:40:55,900 --> 01:40:58,498
I... I wasn't trying
to expose anything.

2063
01:40:58,500 --> 01:40:59,798
I just was poking into it

2064
01:40:59,800 --> 01:41:01,865
to try to figure out
who killed him,

2065
01:41:01,867 --> 01:41:03,498
and now there's
so many goddamn pieces,

2066
01:41:03,500 --> 01:41:05,665
it's like I got
glass in my brain

2067
01:41:05,667 --> 01:41:08,001
and I don't even know
what I'm after anymore.

2068
01:41:09,368 --> 01:41:10,698
I'm sorry for lyin' to you,

2069
01:41:10,700 --> 01:41:12,965
but you gotta believe
what I'm sayin'.

2070
01:41:12,967 --> 01:41:14,466
You're webbed up
in this somehow,

2071
01:41:14,468 --> 01:41:15,932
and you're in danger.

2072
01:41:15,934 --> 01:41:17,565
Can you stay around
here today?

2073
01:41:17,567 --> 01:41:18,798
Gabby's expecting me.

2074
01:41:18,800 --> 01:41:20,598
We're preparing our testimony.

2075
01:41:20,600 --> 01:41:22,101
It's important, but...

2076
01:41:22,633 --> 01:41:24,299
[sighs]

2077
01:41:24,301 --> 01:41:26,765
I need to make arrangements.

2078
01:41:26,767 --> 01:41:28,165
- A funeral.
- Look,

2079
01:41:28,167 --> 01:41:30,065
none of that matters, okay?
If I'm right,

2080
01:41:30,067 --> 01:41:31,665
they're gonna keep a tight lid
on it and they won't even let

2081
01:41:31,667 --> 01:41:33,201
the coroner's office
release his body. Just...

2082
01:41:33,967 --> 01:41:35,032
Please.

2083
01:41:35,034 --> 01:41:36,332
Get one of the guys
from the club

2084
01:41:36,334 --> 01:41:37,965
to take you down to work.

2085
01:41:37,967 --> 01:41:40,531
Stay around people that you
know for the next few days.

2086
01:41:40,533 --> 01:41:42,101
I'll come and find you.

2087
01:41:42,900 --> 01:41:44,034
Okay?

2088
01:41:47,401 --> 01:41:48,965
Ah, okay, okay.

2089
01:41:48,967 --> 01:41:50,999
All right, all right,
all right.

2090
01:41:51,001 --> 01:41:52,032
Take it easy.

2091
01:41:52,034 --> 01:41:53,498
Jeez, they sent
the pros today.

2092
01:41:53,500 --> 01:41:55,767
I must have...
I must have hit a nerve.

2093
01:42:16,567 --> 01:42:18,067
Oh, jeez, thanks.

2094
01:42:23,101 --> 01:42:25,134
Hold this for me,
will you, sweetheart?

2095
01:42:45,234 --> 01:42:47,598
You know who I am?

2096
01:42:47,600 --> 01:42:49,366
I've been asking around
about that.

2097
01:42:49,368 --> 01:42:51,965
Everyone seems to have
a different answer, though.

2098
01:42:51,967 --> 01:42:52,898
[Moses chuckles]

2099
01:42:52,900 --> 01:42:55,366
Spoken like a true snoop.

2100
01:42:55,368 --> 01:42:57,234
Well, what's your take on it?

2101
01:42:58,134 --> 01:42:59,134
Easy.

2102
01:43:01,067 --> 01:43:02,267
I'm a builder.

2103
01:43:03,767 --> 01:43:05,267
Yeah, I can see that.

2104
01:43:06,101 --> 01:43:07,932
When I was a boy,

2105
01:43:07,934 --> 01:43:08,999
you know how many
bridges there were

2106
01:43:09,001 --> 01:43:10,531
on and off Manhattan Island?

2107
01:43:10,533 --> 01:43:12,232
Two.

2108
01:43:12,234 --> 01:43:14,332
A shitty little train trestle
here and the Brooklyn Bridge,

2109
01:43:14,334 --> 01:43:15,798
and when you crossed that,

2110
01:43:15,800 --> 01:43:17,165
you were stepping over manure
much of the way.

2111
01:43:17,167 --> 01:43:19,232
People mostly scuttled
into New York

2112
01:43:19,234 --> 01:43:21,101
off of docks, like rats.

2113
01:43:21,867 --> 01:43:24,531
I built that, and that...

2114
01:43:24,533 --> 01:43:25,800
and that...

2115
01:43:26,234 --> 01:43:27,466
and that.

2116
01:43:27,468 --> 01:43:29,798
And now,
people vault over rivers

2117
01:43:29,800 --> 01:43:32,001
on the spans
and parkways of...

2118
01:43:33,434 --> 01:43:35,898
- Olympus.
- Olympic rat-man!

2119
01:43:35,900 --> 01:43:36,965
Sorry.

2120
01:43:36,967 --> 01:43:38,265
Hmm.

2121
01:43:38,267 --> 01:43:39,598
They're some pretty bridges,
I'll give you that.

2122
01:43:39,600 --> 01:43:40,999
Thank you.

2123
01:43:41,001 --> 01:43:42,466
I want you to give me
something else

2124
01:43:42,468 --> 01:43:43,834
if you can find it.

2125
01:43:45,301 --> 01:43:46,765
Have you found it?

2126
01:43:46,767 --> 01:43:48,099
What's in it?

2127
01:43:48,101 --> 01:43:49,798
Slander, falsehood,

2128
01:43:49,800 --> 01:43:51,232
forgery, most likely.

2129
01:43:51,234 --> 01:43:52,765
Well, then,
the law's on your side.

2130
01:43:52,767 --> 01:43:53,999
You got nothin'
to worry about.

2131
01:43:54,001 --> 01:43:55,732
Very little
I've achieved in my life

2132
01:43:55,734 --> 01:43:57,999
has relied on legality.

2133
01:43:58,001 --> 01:44:01,099
I'm not about to lean
on that slender branch now,

2134
01:44:01,101 --> 01:44:03,065
when things matter most.

2135
01:44:03,067 --> 01:44:04,965
So, you're above the law?
That it?

2136
01:44:04,967 --> 01:44:06,199
No.

2137
01:44:06,201 --> 01:44:07,332
I'm just ahead of it.

2138
01:44:07,334 --> 01:44:08,531
What's the difference?

2139
01:44:08,533 --> 01:44:09,965
Well, the law's a rule book

2140
01:44:09,967 --> 01:44:12,232
we make for the times
we find ourselves in.

2141
01:44:12,234 --> 01:44:14,065
You rebuild the city,
in my experience,

2142
01:44:14,067 --> 01:44:17,032
the law will follow you
and adapt to what you do.

2143
01:44:17,034 --> 01:44:19,199
Yeah, a lot of people like
the city the way it is.

2144
01:44:19,201 --> 01:44:20,267
Who you rebuildin' it for?

2145
01:44:21,234 --> 01:44:22,267
The people to come.

2146
01:44:23,700 --> 01:44:25,631
Fifty, 100 years from now,

2147
01:44:25,633 --> 01:44:28,099
what will matter
of what we've done now?

2148
01:44:28,101 --> 01:44:32,165
What will help people
to make science fiction real?

2149
01:44:32,167 --> 01:44:33,965
The laws of today?

2150
01:44:33,967 --> 01:44:36,199
Or roads and bridges
and tunnels

2151
01:44:36,201 --> 01:44:38,399
for commerce
to move swiftly over?

2152
01:44:38,401 --> 01:44:39,932
Beaches and parks
to let people

2153
01:44:39,934 --> 01:44:42,165
escape the rat race
and inspire the mind?

2154
01:44:42,167 --> 01:44:45,898
Palaces of culture where
hellish slums used to be?

2155
01:44:45,900 --> 01:44:48,565
It all sounds pretty grand,
I guess,

2156
01:44:48,567 --> 01:44:50,466
unless you happen to be
one of the people

2157
01:44:50,468 --> 01:44:53,201
whose house is in the way
right now.

2158
01:44:53,600 --> 01:44:54,867
[scoffs]

2159
01:44:55,533 --> 01:44:57,099
Central Park,

2160
01:44:57,101 --> 01:44:58,832
the greatest urban park
in the world.

2161
01:44:58,834 --> 01:45:00,165
When they started
work on that,

2162
01:45:00,167 --> 01:45:02,265
there wasn't even a city
above 57th Street.

2163
01:45:02,267 --> 01:45:06,199
They kicked out farmers
and tenant squatters,

2164
01:45:06,201 --> 01:45:09,832
sheep-herders out
of muddy fields and filth.

2165
01:45:09,834 --> 01:45:11,466
They moved a few trees.

2166
01:45:11,468 --> 01:45:15,732
And people protested about
the loss of the countryside.

2167
01:45:15,734 --> 01:45:18,698
And if one man hadn't seen
ahead to what we'd need,

2168
01:45:18,700 --> 01:45:21,834
this city would be unlivable,
would it not?

2169
01:45:22,500 --> 01:45:23,700
Yes, it would.

2170
01:45:25,034 --> 01:45:28,032
Most people don't even know
Fred Olmsted's name,

2171
01:45:28,034 --> 01:45:30,101
yet they should thank him
every day.

2172
01:45:31,900 --> 01:45:33,001
I do.

2173
01:45:39,934 --> 01:45:42,999
The important thing in this
life is to get things done.

2174
01:45:43,001 --> 01:45:45,999
Those who can, build.
Those who can't, criticize.

2175
01:45:46,001 --> 01:45:48,765
And I will not obstruct
the great work of this world,

2176
01:45:48,767 --> 01:45:50,531
while some chipmunks
are screeching

2177
01:45:50,533 --> 01:45:52,132
about having to relocate
their nuts.

2178
01:45:52,134 --> 01:45:53,798
Screech a nut, munk-chip.

2179
01:45:53,800 --> 01:45:56,001
Chip a munk's love nuts, man.

2180
01:45:56,500 --> 01:45:57,767
Uh...

2181
01:45:58,734 --> 01:46:00,466
I can't control it, I'm sorry.

2182
01:46:00,468 --> 01:46:01,667
It's all right.

2183
01:46:03,167 --> 01:46:06,798
Talent and brains are rewarded
in this building, Lionel.

2184
01:46:06,800 --> 01:46:09,466
If you're with us,
I'll see to it personally

2185
01:46:09,468 --> 01:46:12,734
that your gifts
are appreciated.

2186
01:46:14,934 --> 01:46:16,834
But that's the offer today.

2187
01:46:18,934 --> 01:46:21,201
You let me know
where you stand by tonight.

2188
01:46:33,567 --> 01:46:35,399
It's funny. We read it wrong.

2189
01:46:35,401 --> 01:46:36,798
[Lionel] How's that?

2190
01:46:36,800 --> 01:46:38,932
We didn't make you for the ace
in Minna's deck.

2191
01:46:38,934 --> 01:46:40,165
Ace-hole!

2192
01:46:40,167 --> 01:46:41,700
Ace-hole!

2193
01:46:48,900 --> 01:46:50,165
- You good?
- No.

2194
01:46:50,167 --> 01:46:52,765
Loosey, goosey,
thread-head fuck!

2195
01:46:52,767 --> 01:46:54,798
Jesus, Lionel. Calm down.

2196
01:46:54,800 --> 01:46:56,332
[Lionel]
It's a missing piece, Danny.

2197
01:46:56,334 --> 01:46:58,032
It's a missing piece
and I can't see it.

2198
01:46:58,034 --> 01:47:00,700
It's makin'
my fuckin' brain hurt.

2199
01:47:14,533 --> 01:47:16,065
Where's the rest?

2200
01:47:16,067 --> 01:47:17,698
- Where's the rest of these?
- They're in the desk,

2201
01:47:17,700 --> 01:47:18,765
but those are the only ones
with her in 'em.

2202
01:47:18,767 --> 01:47:20,032
