02:13:20,267 --> 02:13:21,633
[door closes]

2698
02:13:23,167 --> 02:13:24,832
Son of a bitch!

2699
02:13:24,834 --> 02:13:27,034
[soft music playing]

2700
02:13:54,101 --> 02:13:55,633
[train passing overhead]

2701
02:14:29,967 --> 02:14:32,865
[Lionel] <i>Growin' up, I always
thought Frank was a hero.</i>

2702
02:14:32,867 --> 02:14:35,332
<i>But he was no crusader
in the end.</i>

2703
02:14:35,334 --> 02:14:37,498
<i>He was just a gumshoe
tryin' to make a buck</i>

2704
02:14:37,500 --> 02:14:39,032
<i>like everyone else.</i>

2705
02:14:39,034 --> 02:14:41,199
<i>But he didn't have
to go to that war.</i>

2706
02:14:41,201 --> 02:14:42,999
<i>He was old enough to
have skipped it,</i>

2707
02:14:43,001 --> 02:14:44,565
<i>and he went, anyway,
'cause he actually thought</i>

2708
02:14:44,567 --> 02:14:45,934
<i>this country
was worth fighting for.</i>

2709
02:14:47,368 --> 02:14:49,432
<i>I never had anything
I cared about enough</i>

2710
02:14:49,434 --> 02:14:52,732
<i>to look past my own problems,
but Laura did.</i>

2711
02:14:52,734 --> 02:14:54,332
<i>There was a story
she wanted told</i>

2712
02:14:54,334 --> 02:14:55,999
<i>and I figured it was time</i>

2713
02:14:56,001 --> 02:14:58,399
<i>to get off my ass
and pick a side.</i>

2714
02:14:58,401 --> 02:15:00,732
Hey, Gleason, for you.

2715
02:15:00,734 --> 02:15:02,132
<i>Hey, pal,
I'm new to this beat.</i>

2716
02:15:02,134 --> 02:15:03,466
<i>What's the story here?</i>

2717
02:15:03,468 --> 02:15:05,332
[Gleason] <i>Stories of injustice
and despair,</i>

2718
02:15:05,334 --> 02:15:06,732
<i>and back to business as usual.</i>

2719
02:15:06,734 --> 02:15:08,067
<i>The American way.</i>

2720
02:15:29,934 --> 02:15:31,101
[laughs]

2721
02:15:55,001 --> 02:15:57,134
Are you crazy?
It's freezin' out.

2722
02:15:59,267 --> 02:16:00,633
[sighs]

2723
02:16:03,034 --> 02:16:04,767
[ship horn blows in distance]

2724
02:16:09,734 --> 02:16:11,533
What is this place?

2725
02:16:12,600 --> 02:16:14,332
[clicks tongue]

2726
02:16:14,334 --> 02:16:15,800
It was Frank's.

2727
02:16:19,633 --> 02:16:21,633
And looks like it's mine now.

2728
02:16:33,267 --> 02:16:36,001
Still lookin' out for you,
after all.

2729
02:16:40,633 --> 02:16:42,900
Funny how things turn out.

2730
02:16:45,234 --> 02:16:46,234
Yeah.

2731
02:16:49,167 --> 02:16:50,567
"Brooklyn's big...

2732
02:16:52,201 --> 02:16:54,867
Brooklyn's big, but there's
things even bigger."

2733
02:16:56,533 --> 02:16:57,900
What's that?

2734
02:16:59,867 --> 02:17:02,698
I think it's something
Frank said to me, but I...

2735
02:17:02,700 --> 02:17:04,567
I can't remember when.

2736
02:17:11,667 --> 02:17:14,034
Maybe this is what he meant.

2737
02:17:15,468 --> 02:17:16,667
[Lionel] If!

2738
02:17:17,468 --> 02:17:18,667
If!

2739
02:17:32,468 --> 02:17:33,834
[Lionel sighs]

2740
